abstract = {The main objective of this study was to determine canopy-air temperature
differential, which can be used to quantify crop water stress index
(CWSI) for grapevine (Vitis vinifera L.) grown with drip irrigation
during the spring cultivation period of 2005. Specifically, crop
response to water loss, atmospheric temperature and air vapor pressure
