re Reserve and Sagarmatha National Park on peoples lives, livelihoods, safety, and environments,(2)strengthened integration of the social and physical sciences within the climate change research, analysis, project design, and implementation processes, and(3)strengthened stakeholder capacities to access and use scientific information to better adapt and respond to the risks and vulnerabilities associated with contemporary changes in climate, land use patterns, and tropical high mountain environments.},
author = {Byers, Alton C},
booktitle = {Mountains Witnesses of Global Changes Research in the Himalaya and Karakoram: Share-Asia Project},
doi = {https://doi.org/10.1016/S0928-2025(06)10027-9},
